                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-148" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE GODFREY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of the watch of St. Sepulchre. On we 20th of August the prisoner was brought to the watch-house by a pa<lb></lb>trol—he had given himself up for robbing his master—he stated to me that he had taken a dinner out, and they "had given him a £10 note to take to his master, who gave him the change, and he lost a sovereign, and was afraid to go back to his master.</p>
